  "text": "In a second step, we cluster the features using pairwise-clustering [CITATION_1] based on the pairwise distances d ij = kK i K j k F between all feature pairs using the Frobenius norm. We then compute an optimal matrix T, which contains the pairwise Hamming distances between child labels, i.e., T(s, u) = 0 if s and u belong to the same group 2 {DD, CC}, with CC referring to control, and T(s, u) = 1 otherwise. For each cluster, we select one representative feature, which is the one with the smallest distance dt i = ||K i T|| F to matrix T.",
